fmt
------------------------------------------
fmt is an open-source formatting library for C++. It can be used as a safe and
fast alternative to (s)printf and iostreams.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libfmt-devel-7.0.3-1bl1
  libfmt7-7.0.3-1bl1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-2
  libstdc++6-9.3.0-2
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-2
  ninja-1.10.1-1
  ruby-2.6.4-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/fmtlib/fmt

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/fmtlib/fmt/archive/7.0.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack fmt-7.0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./fmt-7.0.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/fmt-7.0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/fmt-7.0.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfmt7-7.0.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfmt-devel-7.0.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(fmt)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/fmt.README
  /usr/share/doc/fmt/CONTRIBUTING.md
  /usr/share/doc/fmt/ChangeLog.rst
  /usr/share/doc/fmt/LICENSE.rst
  /usr/share/doc/fmt/README.rst

(libfmt7)
  /usr/bin/cygfmt-7.dll

(libfmt-devel)
  /usr/include/fmt/chrono.h
